article.headline: Marquette forces 26 turnovers in victory over Louisville
article.linkText: Marquette forces 26 turnovers in victory over Louisville
article.story:
MILWAUKEE -- Christina Quaye scored 20 points and Krystal
Ellis added 19 to lead No. 21 Marquette to a 65-54 win over Louisville (No. 19 ESPN/USA Today; No. 20 AP) on Saturday.

The Golden Eagles (22-4, 10-3 Big East) led 34-30 at halftime and opened the second half with a 12-1 run.

Marquette forced 26 turnovers and turned them into 23 points.

Angel McCoughtry scored 19 of her 29 points in the first half for Louisville (22-5, 8-5). She also had 10 rebounds and six steals.
